    <p>Ride For Rain­bows: Vir­tual Ride</p>
    <p>Or­gan­ised by Club Rain­bow, Sin­ga­pore’s largest char­ity cy­cling event aims to raise $700,000 for chil­dren with chronic ill­nesses and their fam­i­lies, while also pro­mot­ing health and fit­ness through cy­cling. Rid­ers can cover the dis­tance in one ride or do it over the par­tic­i­pat­ing pe­riod. They can do it out­doors or in­doors and on any bike.</p>
    <p>WHEN: Oct 3 - 11</p>
    <p>AD­MIS­SION: $200 (20km) & $700 (70km) INFO: ride­for­rain­bows.org</p>
    <p>Be­yond The La­bel Fest</p>
    <p>This two-day vir­tual fes­ti­val, which fea­tures mu­sic, workshops and talks, aims to pro­mote sup­port for men­tal well­ness. Learn to tackle men­tal health stigma, and en­cour­age sup­port and ac­cep­tance of peo­ple who are re­cov­er­ing from men­tal health con­di­tions. All do­na­tions go to the Com­mu­nity Chest.</p>
    <p>WHEN: Sept 26 & 27</p>
    <p>AD­MIS­SION: $10 do­na­tion with reg­is­tra­tion for each work­shop</p>
    <p>INFO: bit.ly/3c2boWK</p>


